-- INSERT INTO candles VALUES (NULL, 1, 'Fresh & Clean', 'Lucky Shamrock™ - Returning Favorite', 'https://www.yankeecandle.com/yankee-candle/candles/candle-styles/original-jar-candles/lucky-shamrock---returning-favorite/ORCL_1632868.html', 'This is a Fresh & Clean fragrance. A touch of the Emerald Isle…the fresh scent of lush, green hills kissed by a sparkle of sunshine. Top notes: Green Notes, Zesty Citrus. Middle notes: Eucalyptus, Hyacinth. Base notes: Cedar Wood, Violet Leaf. Top note is the initial impression of the fragrance, middle note is the main body of the scent and base is its final impression.', 4.3, 695, 'As a birthday reward, I decided to treat myself to the Lucky Shamrock™ large jar candle, a returning seasonal favorite. The promise of "fresh grass" was incredibly appealing, especially as we''re still shaking off the last vestiges of winter. And, thankfully, the candle itself delivered. The scent is truly evocative of a freshly mowed lawn on a crisp spring morning. It''s green, clean, and surprisingly refreshing. It fills the room with a light, airy fragrance that''s not overpowering, but definitely noticeable. If you''re a fan of natural, outdoor scents, this one is a winner. It''s a perfect pick-me-up for those dreary days when you''re longing for warmer weather. However, my positive experience with the candle''s fragrance was significantly dampened by the excruciatingly slow order fulfillment. I placed an online order for just this one candle, from a store that is consistently, and I mean consistently, not busy. It took them nearly 72 hours to process and prepare my order for pick-up. For a single candle. In a store that''s usually empty. That''s simply unacceptable. While I understand that seasonal items can create a surge in demand, three days for a single item is beyond reasonable. It completely took the shine off what should have been a delightful birthday treat. Pros: * Authentic "fresh grass" scent, perfect for spring. * Refreshing and not overpowering. * Good throw, fills the room with a pleasant aroma. Cons: * Extremely slow online order fulfillment (nearly 72 hours for a single candle). Overall: The Lucky Shamrock™ candle itself is a lovely seasonal scent that I would happily recommend. However, be prepared for potentially frustratingly slow order fulfillment if you''re ordering online for in-store pickup. If you can snag this candle in person, it''s definitely worth it. But if you have to order online, prepare to be patient.', 5);
